     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0012"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>The following examples are derived from 
     <Em xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0013"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Homology manifold bordism
     </Em>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> by Heather Johnston and Andrew Ranicki (Trans. Amer. Math. Soc. 352 no 11 (2000), PII: S 0002-9947(00)02630-1).
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <Sect xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.0014"
     >
    <section xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0015"
       title="Homology manifold bordism"
       rolemaps-to="H1"
      >
     <section-number xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0016"
        rolemaps-to="Span"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>4 
     </section-number>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Homology manifold bordism
    </section>
    <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0017"
       rolemaps-to="Part"
      >
     <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0018"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
        rolemaps-to="P"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>The results of Johnston [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0019"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>5
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>] on homology manifolds are extended here. It is not possible to investigate transversality by geometric methods—as in [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0020"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>5
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>] we employ bordism and surgery instead.
     </text>
    </text-unit>
    <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0021"
       rolemaps-to="Part"
      >
     <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0022"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
        rolemaps-to="P"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>The proof of transversality is indirect, relying heavily on surgery theory—see Kirby and Siebenmann [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0023"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>7
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>, III, §1], Marin [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0024"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>8
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>] and Quinn [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0025"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>11
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>]. We shall use the formulation in terms of topological block bundles of Rourke and Sanderson [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0026"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>12
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>].
     </text>
    </text-unit>
    <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0027"
       rolemaps-to="Part"
      >
     <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0028"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
        rolemaps-to="P"
       >
      <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0029"
         title="math"
         af="mathml-1.xml tag-AFfile1.tex"
         xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
         Layout:Placement="Inline"
        >
        <AssociatedFile name="mathml-1.xml" xmlns="">
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑄</mi> </math>
        </AssociatedFile>
        <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile1.tex" xmlns="">
        $Q$
        </AssociatedFile>
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑄
      </Formula>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> is a codimension 
      <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0030"
         title="math"
         af="mathml-2.xml tag-AFfile2.tex"
         xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
         Layout:Placement="Inline"
        >
        <AssociatedFile name="mathml-2.xml" xmlns="">
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑞</mi> </math>
        </AssociatedFile>
        <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile2.tex" xmlns="">
        $q$
        </AssociatedFile>
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑞
      </Formula>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> subspace by Theorem 4.9 of Rourke and Sanderson [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0031"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>12
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>]. (Hughes, Taylor and Williams [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0032"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>4
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>] obtained a topological regular neighborhood theorem for arbitrary submanifolds ….)
     </text>
    </text-unit>
    <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0033"
       rolemaps-to="Part"
      >
     <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0034"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
        rolemaps-to="P"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Wall [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0035"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>13
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>, Chapter 11] obtained a codimension 
      <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0036"
         title="math"
         af="mathml-2.xml tag-AFfile3.tex"
         xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
         Layout:Placement="Inline"
        >
        <AssociatedFile name="mathml-2.xml" xmlns="">
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑞</mi> </math>
        </AssociatedFile>
        <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile3.tex" xmlns="">
        $q$
        </AssociatedFile>
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑞
      </Formula>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> splitting obstruction ….
     </text>
    </text-unit>
    <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0037"
       rolemaps-to="Part"
      >
     <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0038"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
        rolemaps-to="P"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>… following the work of Cohen [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0039"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>2
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>] on 
      <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0040"
         title="math"
         af="mathml-4.xml tag-AFfile4.tex"
         xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
         Layout:Placement="Inline"
        >
        <AssociatedFile name="mathml-4.xml" xmlns="">
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑃</mi> <mi>𝐿</mi> </math>
        </AssociatedFile>
        <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile4.tex" xmlns="">
        $PL$
        </AssociatedFile>
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑃𝐿
      </Formula>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> manifold transversality.
     </text>
    </text-unit>
    <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0041"
       rolemaps-to="Part"
      >
     <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0042"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
        rolemaps-to="P"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>In this case each inverse image is automatically a 
      <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0043"
         title="math"
         af="mathml-4.xml tag-AFfile5.tex"
         xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
         Layout:Placement="Inline"
        >
        <AssociatedFile name="mathml-4.xml" xmlns="">
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑃</mi> <mi>𝐿</mi> </math>
        </AssociatedFile>
        <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile5.tex" xmlns="">
        $PL$
        </AssociatedFile>
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑃𝐿
      </Formula>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> submanifold of codi
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>mension 
      <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0044"
         title="math"
         af="mathml-6.xml tag-AFfile6.tex"
         xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
         Layout:Placement="Inline"
        >
        <AssociatedFile name="mathml-6.xml" xmlns="">
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝜎</mi> </math>
        </AssociatedFile>
        <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile6.tex" xmlns="">
        $\sigma $
        </AssociatedFile>
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝜎
      </Formula>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> (Cohen [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0045"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>2
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>]), so there is no need to use 
      <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0046"
         title="math"
         af="mathml-7.xml tag-AFfile7.tex"
         xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
