    <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0056"
       rolemaps-to="Part"
      >
     <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0057"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
        rolemaps-to="P"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>For 
      <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0058"
         title="math"
         af="mathml-8.xml tag-AFfile8.tex"
         xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
         Layout:Placement="Inline"
        >
        <AssociatedFile name="mathml-8.xml" xmlns="">
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑚</mi> <mo lspace="0.278em" rspace="0.278em">≥</mo> <mn>5</mn> </math>
        </AssociatedFile>
        <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile8.tex" xmlns="">
        $m\geq 5$
        </AssociatedFile>
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑚≥5
      </Formula>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> the Novikov-Wall surgery theory for topological manifolds gives an exact sequence (Wall [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0059"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>13
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>, Chapter 10].
     </text>
    </text-unit>
    <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0060"
       rolemaps-to="Part"
      >
     <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0061"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
        rolemaps-to="P"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>The surgery theory of topological manifolds was extended to homology man
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>ifolds in Quinn [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0062"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>9
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>, 
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0063"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>10
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>] and Bryant, Ferry, Mio and Weinberger [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0064"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>1
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>].
     </text>
    </text-unit>
    <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0065"
       rolemaps-to="Part"
      >
     <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0066"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
        rolemaps-to="P"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>The 4-periodic obstruction is equivalent to an 
      <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0067"
         title="math"
         af="mathml-9.xml tag-AFfile9.tex"
         xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
         Layout:Placement="Inline"
        >
        <AssociatedFile name="mathml-9.xml" xmlns="">
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑚</mi> </math>
        </AssociatedFile>
        <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile9.tex" xmlns="">
        $m$
        </AssociatedFile>
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑚
      </Formula>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>-dimensional homology man
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>ifold, by [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0068"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>1
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>].
     </text>
    </text-unit>
    <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0069"
       rolemaps-to="Part"
      >
     <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0070"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
        rolemaps-to="P"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Thus, the surgery exact sequence of [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0071"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>1
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>] does not follow Wall [
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0072"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>13
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>] in relating homology manifold structures and normal invariants.
     </text>
    </text-unit>
    <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0073"
       rolemaps-to="Part"
      >
     <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0074"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
        rolemaps-to="P"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>… the canonical 
      <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0075"
         title="math"
         af="mathml-10.xml tag-AFfile10.tex"
         xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
         Layout:Placement="Inline"
        >
        <AssociatedFile name="mathml-10.xml" xmlns="">
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑇</mi> <mi>𝑂</mi> <mi>𝑃</mi> </math>
        </AssociatedFile>
        <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile10.tex" xmlns="">
        $TOP$
        </AssociatedFile>
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑇𝑂𝑃
      </Formula>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> reduction ([
      <Link xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0076"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>3
       <?ReferencedObject type="Annot" page="1" ?>
      </Link>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>]) of the Spivak normal fibration of 
      <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
         id="ID.0077"
         title="math"
         af="mathml-11.xml tag-AFfile11.tex"
         xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
